caption: Delicious chili cheese fries. Wish they had a safer setup with a private entrance during covid so you didn’t have to walk through the entirety of Whole Foods to get their food.

I LOVE THIS PLACE! I mean even if your not into veganism I’m sure you will enjoy the food here. The spicy chicken sandwich is my favorite. The burgers are great also. And the oat milk shake is defiantly my go to treat. The drinks are exotic and tasty also. The fries could use a bit less salt but are still very good especially with the sauces (they all are good). The customer service is always great too. Defiantly one of my favorite spots and would love for it to expand into more Whole Foods.
Obsessed! It’s like a vegan In-N-Out. I also watched them fill my small fries, put them in the bag, the add more fries on top. Not all heroes wear capes.
Today I was at plnt burger and haves great customer service, they are clean and are well organized. Keep it up!

Came in this past week to try out this good Burger place I've heard so much about. My friends and I were greeted with smiles. The burgers were so delicious and the customer service above my expectation. The manager Jacqueline was amazing and super sweet, she had one of the best customer services I have ever seen. I'll definitely come back to this location and recommend to anyone!

I stopped by with my wife and kids to try this place out because I’ve heard great things about it , food was delicious and exceeded my expectations. To top it off I was handled so great by the manager , I believe her name was Jaquelíne , it’s always good to have the customer service at a level of the quality of the food and I personally loved it. I will be back again with my family and I will always love to have ms Jaquelíne take care of us. Thank you guys ! Great job

Tried the new Spicy Chik’n Funguy sandwich, which they were giving away for free to the first 100 customers today. It was delicious, fresh, and pretty spicy! The “chicken” was made out of a mushroom I believe, which doesn’t exactly mimic the texture of meat but it doesn’t make you miss chicken at all because it had so much flavor and was fried perfectly! I also got a side of Bloomies with sweet chili sauce, which was extremely tasty. I picked up a Carrot-Oat-Pineapple cookie as well, which sounded interesting and turned out to be sooo good! The staff was extremely friendly and I will definitely be returning to try out some more menu items. (:
